node.text:
Our plans have changed, but our determination remains the same 🇺🇸 We might not be in Tokyo right now, but we will use this extra time to push ourselves to be citius, altius, fortius next year💪🏼

So grateful for this @poloralphlauren One-Year-Out Collection that supports @TeamUSA and helps us prepare to be our best 👊🏼

Check out the collection at the link in my bio ⭐️

node.text: Victoria gets REAL with me about her experience with binge eating, body image, and how being a college athlete can take a toll on your mental health. We talk about how she dealt with these challenges and her pathway to therapy and the help we all need from time to time. We end with some tips for performing under pressure, so you don’t want to miss that! My hope is that you all walk away with something that will help you improve your own mental health and remember you are NEVER alone!

node.title: Body Image, Mental Health & More with Victoria Garrick!

node.text: I had a little time on my hands today so I scrolled through my camera roll and threw together this video🤗 Grateful for all these times and these humans and can’t wait to make more memories! ❤️ @alixklineman @jenniferkessy & * @fiapogtenius we need some video with you! 🙈

Can always count on partner-to-coach @jenniferkessy for a balance of intensity and lightheartedness, to tell it like it is, and of course entertain us in the process 🤣 Grateful to have her on our team! 🙏🏼🙌🏼❤️ Enjoy this look at what goes on in our player box during a big match 👊🏼 (also don’t think my Gatorade matching my suit was a coincidence 💁🏼‍♀️) •••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••
Repost from @avpbeach

For the first time, we take you behind-the-scenes and in the coach's corner. Get an inside look at the coaching process and commentary of Olympic Silver Medalist and #AVP coach, @JenniferKessy, as she led the #ATeam into the Women's Final of the 2019 #AVPGoldSeries // Manhattan Beach Open.

node.text:
The last few days here in Tokyo have been super busy preparing for competition to start! Lots of training, lots of recovery, lots of food, and lots of excitement! (And definitely lots of pin trading 🤗) 

This morning we got to practice on center court with our fellow Americans, the stadium is beautiful 😍 And we had to make the very tough decision of which color combos ❤️🤍💙 in our competition suits we were going to name our first, second, and third choices- any guesses? Apparently we have way more color combo options than any other team 🤷🏼‍♀️🤣

📸1: @charlie_riedel_pix 👊🏼

node.text: Explored the village today🤩 Can report- the food is great 🙌🏼 the AC is flowing☃️ the plaza is adorable🏮the gym is top notch💯 the views are 😍🌇🌉 and the #TeamUSA facilities and staff are amazing❤️🤍💙 so grateful to be here 🤗

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by April Ross on July 16, 2021 tagging @kttape. May be an image of 1 person and standing.

node.text:
When the training intensity increases so can the aches and pains, but thankfully I have my @kttape Recovery+ Wave to help minimize any pain that I might be feeling. Lately I’ve been using my Wave on an attachment near my hip that became irritated at our training camp in Florida and it’s feeling so much better 🙌🏼 

Thank you @kttape for helping us deal with the grind as we prepare for Tokyo!!👊🏼👊🏼👊🏼

📸: @amoorephoto_ ⚡️

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by April Ross on July 14, 2021 tagging @alixklineman, and @poloralphlauren. May be an image of 2 people, people standing and suit.

node.text:
The Olympic and Paralympic Games are just around the corner so you know what that means- Opening Ceremony!🎉 I am beyond proud and excited to partner with @PoloRalphLauren as a #RLxTeamUSA athlete, not least of all because I get to be a part of this reveal! 🤗
 
Designed in red, white, and blue, #PoloRalphLauren unveils our Team USA Opening ceremony uniform featuring official USA patches and the iconic Polo Pony.
 
Follow along here on the road to Tokyo🗼and learn more about how #PoloRalphLauren supports Team USA.
 
#TeamUSA ❤️🤍💙

Rule 40 goes into effect on Tuesday so I won’t be able to show my love to certain partners while I’m in Tokyo, but if you’d like to support me and one of my longest standing sponsors you can purchase something from my ARxMizuno line🙏🏼 (the pieces I’m wearing in the photo plus more!) The link is in my bio- mizunousa.com 👊🏼

Thanks as always for your support in all its forms!❤️
